#!/usr/bin/env -S mcphost script
---
model: ollama:qwen2.5-coder:7b
maxSteps: 60
approveToolRun: true

# You pass args on the command line:
#   --args:target example.com
#   --args:program acme
#   --args:workdir /home/sbu/bb
#   --args:shodan_query 'hostname:example.com'
args:
  target: "${target}"
  program: "${program:-default}"
  workdir: "${workdir:-/home/sbu/bb}"
  shodan_query: "${shodan_query:-}"

systemPrompt: |
  You are an assistant running an authorized security assessment.
  Do not run any actions unless they are in-scope for the provided target.
  Prefer low-impact recon and report generation. Write all outputs to disk.

prompt: |
  Target: ${target}
  Program: ${program}
  Workspace: ${workdir}/${program}/${target}

  Create this directory structure using filesystem:
    ${workdir}/${program}/${target}/
      scope/
      recon/raw/
      recon/clean/
      recon/live/
      vuln/nuclei/
      intel/shodan/
      report/
      logs/

  Write a file ${workdir}/${program}/${target}/scope/target.txt containing ${target}.
  Create report skeleton files:
    report/summary.md
    report/assets.md
    report/recon.md
    report/findings.md
    report/repro.md
    report/mitigations.md
    report/timeline.md

  Save a memory key "bb.current" with value "${program}:${target}".

  Recon phase (ProjectDiscovery MCP):
    1) Enumerate subdomains for ${target}. Save raw output to recon/raw/subfinder.txt.
    2) Probe discovered hosts for HTTP(S). Save raw output to recon/raw/httpx.txt.
    3) Normalize/clean host list into recon/clean/hosts.txt (one host per line).
    4) Crawl discovered live hosts (katana if available). Save to recon/raw/katana.txt.
       Extract URLs into recon/clean/urls.txt.

  Vulnerability triage phase (ProjectDiscovery MCP):
    5) Run nuclei against recon/clean/hosts.txt with a conservative rate.
       Save results to vuln/nuclei/nuclei.txt.

  Enrichment phase (Shodan MCP) — only if ${shodan_query} is not empty:
    6) Run the Shodan query "${shodan_query}" and save results summary to intel/shodan/shodan.md.

  Reporting phase (filesystem + sequentialthinking):
    7) In report/recon.md: summarize subdomain count, live hosts count, top technologies observed.
    8) In report/findings.md: summarize nuclei findings grouped by severity/template.
       If no findings, say so and list next manual checks to perform.
    9) In report/summary.md: write an executive summary (scope, methods, key outcomes).
    10) In report/timeline.md: write a timestamped log of actions performed.

  End by writing a one-paragraph "Next Actions" section in report/summary.md that lists:
    - highest-value manual followups from the recon artifacts
    - what evidence to capture for any suspected issues
---
